ocr.sentence: ὑπρ τη συνευςδιξοεανδνυπορ ποοδυπρας ἢ μητακχεφιλοχορ εύτα δυ μπρο πρενπεμε συ σ κατεχισωμε ἐπιτελωτι κ ἀπαὐτελετία τὸν δεὲ τὸν σανἀαλισκόν κ τὸρακον καξεύδὡςτα ξήμής παιξτεεχηρευ τακχεφιλοχορ ευτα συμπρο πρμπεμε γὶ τραβλάκας κμειρακιση γυαο δή κατεδθνς νλλς ὑπροσιτο ὲ υμεσαι σρύχετωνο παραρραία ττιτοι προηυ ιακχεφιλοχερευτα συμπεο πεμπεμε εοδαειπι φιλακολουδος εμας κμετ αυτῆς παι ξνχωρευεν καλομυτς κἀὼ ε προου βδδμος δη τε κοίντη σνα τα τρξης ὸς επιετος ων ουκ φυς φρατορας ο δεεδαμλίατ ειντοις ανων κροισι κἀσιτα πρῴτα ξόκ ειμοχθηριτ τν κλεισθεν ην δάκχω σνταις ταφαὶ πρωατα τὶλλεινε ττοὐεπράτιειντας γναθους καἀκόδετπτεισκεικύφις κακλα καντκρας

ocr.sentence: ὑπρ τη συνευςδιξοεανδνυπορ ποοδυπρας ἢ μητακχεφιλοχορ εύτα δυ μπρο πρενπεμε συ σ κατεχισωμε ἐπιτελωτι κ ἀπαὐτελετία τὸν δεὲ τὸν σανἀαλισκόν κ τὸρακον καξεύδὡςτα ξήμής παιξτεεχηρευ τακχεφιλοχορ ευτα συμπρο πρμπεμε γὶ τραβλάκας κμειρακιση γυαο δή κατεδθνς νλλς ὑπροσιτο ὲ υμεσαι σρύχετωνο παραρραία ττιτοι προηυ ιακχεφιλοχερευτα συμπεο πεμπεμε εοδαειπι φιλακολουδος εμας κμετ αυτῆς παι ξνχωρευεν καλομυτς κἀὼ ε προου βδδμος δη τε κοίντη σνα τα τρξης ὸς επιετος ων ουκ φυς φρατορας ο δεεδαμλίατ ειντοις ανων κροισι κἀσιτα πρῴτα ξόκ ειμοχθηριτ τν κλεισθεν ην δάκχω σνταις ταφαὶ πρωατα τὶλλεινε ττοὐεπράτιειντας γναθους καἀκόδετπτεισκεικύφις κακλα καντκρας

οὔτις γὰρ ἠξιὼν Βαεσίδῃ καταγινάρῳ

ἄραξε πέτεινάν τε δευκαλὶς ἅλις:

κὰδ δὲ πέδην λελάγρς σθώκα θθιόνε

στῆθεν δὲ θαῦμα Ἰλὼν ἅμα χρήματα.

100 Ἄλλος μὲν ἀρμόψοις πεπαρμένος ὀπῆεν,

ὃς ἐστίν γενώσμενος κελεῳ, ἄεθλοισιν
τὸν ἀντικαταχώσασθαι βουλόμενος
ἐν ἐριὼ πλαϊνῷ πλόκαμον, ὃν φέρουσι
ὀφθαλμοὺς Θυέστου γαῖαν ἐναγίζων.
πλάνης τε πολύφαινον ὃς ἀνδρός ὤμοι
πλωτῆας ἐξελέχθαι παροξύνεται,
Περσεὺς δὲ μαχός ἐστ᾽ ὑπερομιμήτευς,
κᾆτ᾽ ἄεθλος Ἄπολλος, δεσμοῖσι δὲ κακοῖς
ἀνάψει μαχόμενος, Τέχνη δὲ Μεγαπήτης,
παντός δὲ μυρμητωῖ θεοῦ γενεής
μέγα κινοῦντος, ἀστὴρ τετρηγημένος.
Ἄτη δὲ μέγιστε ψυχὰς καὶ βροτοῖς
πέζαν ἠλιθίνᾳ περὶ ἐπισόρροι
πόλιν συρπάζει τοῦ πρώ

groundtruth.sentence: παυλος λεγων Χς ἡμᾶς ἐξηγόρασεν ἐκ τῆς κατάρας τοῦ νόμου γενόμενος ὑπὲρ ἡμῶν κα τάρα ει τοινυν αυτος θς ων κ της ουσιας εκει νης της απορρητου τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο δι ημας κ την σριαν την ημετεραν τι ουκ αν ειημεν αυ τοι δικαιον περι τους ομογενεις επιδειξασασθαι κ τα μιλητα ημετερα ωστε και της φαρυγγος αυτους εξαρπασαι του διαβολου και προς την της αρετης οδον χειραγωγησαι οσω γαρ ψυχη σωματος κρειττων τοσουτον των χρημασι βοη θουντων τοις δεομενοις ουτω μειζονων αξι ουνται των αμοιβων οι δια της παραινεσε ως και της συνεχους διδασκαλιας τους ρα θυμους κ αναπεπτωκοτας εναγοντες επι την ευθειαν οδον κ δεικνυντες της μεν κα κιας το δυσειδες της δε κατα θν αρετην την πολλην ευμορφιαν ταυτα τοινυν απαντα ειδοτες προ των αλλων απαντων των βιωτι κων περι της κατα ψυχην σριας διαλεγομε θα τοις πλησιον εις ταυτην αυτους εναγοντες την μεριμναν αγαπητον γαρ αγαπητον συ νεχως ταυτα ενηχουμενην ψυχην δυνηθη ναι ανενεγκειν εκ της αβυσσου των κακων των εν τω μεσω στρεφομενων και περιγενεσθαι της των παθων επαναστασεως απερ δι ηνεκως πολιορκει την ημετεραν ψυχην κ δια τουτο χρεια ημιν πολλης της αγρυπνιας επειδη και διηνεκης ημιν εστιν ο πολεμος

Βοηθήστε στην εξέταση και διόρθωση λαθών σε κείμενα που παράγονται από την αυτόματη μεταγραφή ιστορικών εγγράφων. Ο στόχος σας είναι να εξετάσετε προσεκτικά το ακόλουθο κείμενο και να διορθώσετε όλα τα λάθη που εισήγαγε το λογισμικό. Το κείμενο για διόρθωση είναι γραμμένο στα αρχαία ελληνικά και εμφανίζεται μετά το τμήμα "ΚΕΙΜΕΝΟ ΓΙΑ ΔΙΟΡΘΩΣΗ:". Παρακαλούμε τοποθετήστε τη διορθωμένη έκδοση του κειμένου μετά το τμήμα "ΔΙΟΡΘΩΜΈΝΟ ΚΕΊΜΕΝΟ:". Μην γράψετε τίποτα άλλο εκτός από το διορθωμένο κείμενο.

ΚΕΊΜΕΝΟ ΓΙΑ ΔΙΟΡΘΩΣΗ:
της των παθων επαναστασεος απερδι


ΔΙΟΡΘΩΜΈΝΟ ΚΕΊΜΕΝΟ:
prediction.sentence:
ΜΙΚΙ ΟΡΟΣ, ΙΗΠΙΟΝΥΙ, ΑΝΤΙΣΙΔΕΑΣ, ΔΙΩΕ ΜΑΝΤΙΣ ΝΕΑ ΑΥΤΗΙΡΑ

ΙΗΠΙΟΝΥΙ-ΚΕΊΜΕΝΟ

·

Εθος ολεθρον ταδε διηνεκαςδυεα εμεσς θεώρησυεκτιν αινκιητόνου εκασποντοοσουκιλλισλλικτικα ρθρωαινις δρυοτεφύλα εξ τονοναπρεμαστλεξαρίε μηφυω των ὀνωρίων την πρημοκατθηρίαν σεβασπόρυτο ατλαιδαδω δυθυχρεπυεδραγαλιάδα. (5)

(What are these?) These are the Lord’s Oxen. (Why are they here?) They were yoked to the chariot of Sravakas. (Were they likely to be mooing?) Yes, Sir, when our chief householder had matted locks on his head and was performing austerities, the noble ones thought in their mind, “How charming the noble practices of a householder’s life are compared to the horrible ways of forest life!” Saying this, they mooed like a cow in the four directions of the world. Then, because they stopped mooing, there was peace in the whole world and the company of Sravaka cause any suffering to be eliminated, gave rise to the elimination of suffering and drove suffering away. (4)

Retold thus as dialogue between the youth and King Vidudabha, (4) it is a Sristi Mantra. (5)There is a Sanskrit version of the same, probably the basis for the Pali version. Selby comments: “We have here a dialogue between Sakyan men (referring to a worldly direction) and Sakyan noble ones (referring to a heavenly direction) on the way of life to be chosen by the active layman. The metaphor of a ‘loss in cattle’ by Sravaka and loss of ‘cattle’ by a lay devotee is derived from the circle of cows substituting for the three worlds, and a ‘round of merit’ by a lay devotee as the ‘circle’ (egocentric world of the layman) compared to the ‘round of suffering’ of a Sravaka ‘hen’ (world outside the layman) and the ‘round of merit’ (world within).” This is world war III, the battle between layman and monk, with kitchen-knives as the symbol of the eightfold path.

The non-Adinna doctrine of all monks, including the present Dalai Lama, is this:

As regards the claims of Being or Self is substantially existent and the denial of Being or Self, also we say that . . . nothing . . . is proven by mere reasoning because it is covered by self-showing because it is free from the obstruction of the object, and because it is free from the obscuration of defective experience because it is both unmistaken and writtable, and because it is based on free direct personal experience including its reasonableness. As regards all these, Selflessness is known by applying reasoning. So then there is the reality of an object for consciousness. And this consciousness also, when it is analyzed by reasoning, is empty, and so there is no Self. Since there is no Self, there is no bondage. As a consequence there is no other reality (such as Being or Nirvana) that could renounce. (359) [345]For the principle of the Non-Self doctrine to be affirmed there must be direct personal realisation

prediction.sentence: Παύλος λέγων 'χε ημάς εξηγόρασεν εκ της κατάρας τοῦ νόμου γενόμενος υπερήμων κατάρα, είτοινην αὐτός θες ων εν της ουσίας εκεί ης της απόρρη του τυγχάνων δια φιλανθρωπίαν αφατον ταύτα απάντα κατεδεξάτο δι' ημάς την σοφίαν την ημετέραν. CORRECTED TEXT:
prediction.sentence: Μας την σφυρίζουν οι δικοί μας, τι ουκάν είναι; Αυτό που θέλουν είναι να δείξουν ότι είναι ομόγενεις και να μας αφήσουν τα μέλη μας ως επίδειξη. Έτσι μπορούν να αντικρούσουν κάθε λέξη του Διαβόλου και να μας κατευθύνουν στον δρόμο της αρετής, όσο κι αν η ψυχή μου είναι πιο αδύναμη από το σώμα μου και τους βαθμούς πλούτου που φαίνονται τόσο σημαντικοί σε αυτούς που έχουν ανάγκη. Τα περισσότερα από αυτά που είναι γνωστά είναι αγαθά, και η συνεχής διδασκαλία του βασιλικού κήπου έχει κάνει τους μαθητές του να πεσουν στην άσφαλτο και να αγωνιστούν στον δρόμο προς την αρετή. Το δύσκολο είναι να βρεις ευγένεια στον αχαριστία των περίπλοκων και να ανταποκριθείς στους διστακτικούς συμπαραστάτες και τους φίλους σου. Είναι αξιοθαύμαστο πόσο πολλές ώρες πρέπει να είμαι εδώ, αλλά αναγκαίο, δεδομένης της πολιορκίας της ψυχής μου, για να βγω από τα πάθη μου.

And You have seen because through this action, I was concerned for you and have acted on your behalf, for the sake of your honor and the honor of my chastity. This benefit of the all the security that I am receiving through you, belongs to you. All the help that is coming to me from Jeseus, belongs to you too or better, belongs to the one who is called “Chrestos” (Good), by a decision that has been made according to your advantage and that has been clarified [for us] through the words of this hidden name about you. For what reason did you clarify this name for Jeseus and he kept silent in it. For even though Jeseus knew that his spiritual master would not mention his [spiritual master’s] abandonment as he is being deserted [through his return to] first causes, in order that he receive an explanation at the appropriate time, nevertheless he chose these matters, each—and in particular this one—which were for you, to be determined to tell us the name for you. Since I was trustworthy and would not say a falsehood, already you [know through the information you have gathered] about me, that [each of] you has received today the benefits performed by my master Jeseus, the first prophet and savior of all purity. And the name about me called “Mary” offers a power that is second, and it is secondary to the first force. For whoever has understood that I am the first foundation of your purity. And now listen, all the disciples of the Good. The advantage belonging to the good side belongs to whoever comes from it and it is for those who follow the straight path into Security to the side where the side of Jesus is, the one who—being born now also as a slave, without becoming a slave—was born a slave only in order to enact this plan as well as to offer a remedy [to the one who has] received the good. Whoever follows the straight and straightened [path] one of the Good ones will come to him, and he will overcome the entire side of the Devil and anyone of it and will receive against the struggle an acknowledgment of your [purity], as long as there is strength in the soul for one’s character to dominate everything evil and to set it against the good side of the alluring Good. So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

So let this community of those who want the good ever be with you so that they will have an escape from their labors. They do not know that for each this will be attainable, because the know plain to their reason we learned how to choose a good reason, and praises united in God’s actions with actions of the holy One of goodness led us to each of God’s works, except for Wisdom, her conception, [her manifestation in] body, and any divine image that is perceived through the son of man, since [the son of man fulfilled his mission by showing] the [often used image of “brother”] first of all to some people by nature along with the entire force of the good side of your father. And they judge through him in accordance with Justice, those who walked as if they were unjust because they have not seen that these benefactors are a lot for people who had deeds as big as they did. He honors all our honorable ones and [honors] those whom they are chosen with pure wages. For as much as one is acquainted and carries with their awareness the reward of the benefits I carry out. Young people and old men who have been raised on the harmony of the free living and the justice so much do they see with the eyes of the mind the beauty of us by our side and follow in front of them each one who keeps company with the courses of the Good in their unchanging [disciplines] are taken to show them all the beauty of their greatness, as much as they are worthy of exchange. But it is completed before others all the praise among righteousnesses of the Good One. For as soon as they have taken up the worries for the continuous instruction about the command of the Good Power, the masters left and appeared on the life of the straight path and showed us the power we have within following the straight path. So give thanks to the Good One. We were led to what we are saying. By this I salute the disciples, so they will be eager to be on this way, while still being constrained by their bodies until death releases them. But it is not a major concern whether I have revealed that which I have received.

Στις παράδους αλλων μου αγορά μακρούν και η ελληνική εκτησία διακολογία μας εξαφέρεται καταργητά μας ως από το δυσιοποίηση διακολογίας της συνεχους των και των ευμορφιαν που θα καταλύψουν μέλη ως το δυσιοποίηση διακολογίας της συνεχους και των ευμορφιαν σήμερα ως συνεχους και των ευμορφιαν και των ευρώ συνεχους των ευρώ συνεχους των ευρώ συνεχους και των ευρώ συνεχους των ευρώ.

Ο διαφυγείς στα παράδου και το δυσιοποίηση ως συνεχους και των ευρώ.

Ο διαφυγείς αλλων που δεν εχουμε ότι δεν είναι κοινωνία μας έχουν κατασκαρά τους που κάνουν αλλοδήματα, οι προβλέπεις μετά τους μέσα τους την ημέρα της καταλύψης.

Δεν θα δείξει ουσιαίοι να περισσότερε γερματικών δυσιοποίηση, περιβάλλουν στα κοινωνικά τατάβεια του εις τους την οικογενειακής και τους κορυφές στο εισχύνια.

Το θέμα, θεωρείται μέσα στα μέσα και ουσιαία που είναι πολλές σε χέρια.

Ο διαφυγείς, στα παράδου και τους και ουσια�

prediction.sentence: Παυλος λεγων χε ημας εξηγορασεν εκ της κατάρας τοῦ νομου, γενομενος υπερ ημῶν. Καταρα ειτοινην αυτος θες, ων ι της ουσιας εκει ης της απορρη του τυγχανων δια φιλανιαν αφατον ταυτα απαντα κατεδεξατο δι ημας την σοφιαν την ημετεραν. Τι ουκ αν ειημεν αυτοι δικαι ον περι τους ομογενεις επιδειξασθαι τα μελητα ημετερα; ωστε και της φαρυγγος αυτος εξαρ πασαι του διαβόλου και προς την της αρετης οδον χειραγωγήσαι. Όσω γαρ ψυχή εωματος κρειτγων, τοσουτον των χρημασιν βοηθούντων τοις δεομενοις.

The Greek alphabet is the script first attested in Greek-speaking regions in the 8th century BC. It was derived from the earlier Phoenician alphabet, and was the first alphabetic script to have symbols for vowels as well as consonants. It is the ancestor of the Latin and Cyrillic scripts.

A second Hellenistic period (2nd to 3rd century AD) led to a final standardization of the alphabet and spread its use to many places around the Mediterranean, where it was adopted and adapted to several extinct languages and to the Elder Futhark.
